<bug>
    <id>92956</id>
    <title>backup file is deleted after exit, if file was not saved</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">1 start open office writer</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.2">2 type some text</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.3">3 (do not click on save)</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.4">3 (after some time), backup file is created in backup dir, with extension .</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.5">odt</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.6">4 after exiting program, without saving file (do you wish to save file - no), backup file is deleted.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">expected result</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">-backup file is not deleted</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">reason</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.2">-people sometimes absent-mindedly click on no, and lose their work.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">There could be another option in the options/load save:
'make backup of files that are not saved'
so people can turn this on if they want.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">Thanks.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
